This paper focuses on the usability and security implications of third-party skills on Amazon Alexa, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The study also involves analyzing user behavior and perception, which falls under social and information sciences (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential privacy risks associated with third-party skills, which relates to cybercrime (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes design recommendations to improve user understanding, which involves natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
